An alleged armed robbery suspect was apprehended and a vehicle believed to be used in the commission of crimes was recovered when crimefighters got wind of a police pursuit along the N2. The suspects were were heading towards Amanzimtoti, when they were cut off by members of ET Rapid Response who joined law enforcement in the high speed chase. Tony Lokker, spokesperson for the security company, said: “The wanted vehicle was pursued as it passed Galleria mall, when the suspect suddenly lost control of the vehicle and ended up stationary on the center median.” He added: “One suspect was arrested by our TRT and the vehicle used in the commission of offenses was recovered. Further investigations are ongoing for further linkages and arrests of outstanding suspects.”